 :n rt 90 fd 360 lt 180\nEND\n\n;--------------\n\nTO number :n \nrepeat (420)/(:n) [column :n]\nEND\n\n\n;----------------\n\nTO go_to_point :x :y  \nsetxy :x :y\nEND\n\ncleartext\n;go_to_point\n;-----------------\n\nTO random_point\nprint 'x'\nprint (random 20)+ 10*(random 5 )-5\nprint 'y'\nprint (random 10)-8*(random 20)+10\nEND\n\nrandom_point\n\nTO blue\nsetpencolor[0 0 255]\nEnd\n\nTo black \nsetpencolor[0 0 0]\nend \n\nTO light_blue\nsetpencolor[25 93 195]\nend \n\n\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.2246467991473532e-14,"z":200},"character":"Bird","notes":" \n\n            CONSTRUCTING RIGHT TRIANGLES\n\t\t                  *******************************************\n\n   Task\n.............................\n1.  First, define and run the following commands: \n\t\t\tcleartext\n\t\t\taxes\n                        grid 20\n                     \nThen complete the procedure \"right_triangle1\" in order to construct a right triangle with sides length 12, 16 and 20 steps.  \n\n2. Starting from the different coordinates printed at the bottom area of the editor, every time you run the procedure \"start\", construct a right triangle with sides length 30,40 and 50 steps. \n  First, go to the procedure \"right_triangle3\" and complete the command \n                       \"pu go_to_point ..... ...... pd\"\n  \nwith the coordinates printed by the procedure \"start\". Then complete the rest of the commands in a way that would allow you to construct the requested right triangle.\n\n3. Starting from the different coordinates printed at the bottom area of the editor, every time you run the procedure \"start\", construct a right triangle with sides length 45,60 and 75 steps. Act the same way as case 2. \n\n                            ------------------------------\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t          TIPS\n\t\t            ------------------------------\n\n   What known theorem is requested in order to construct a right triangle in every case? \n\n * In any case,